				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">The Vile Politics of the Syrian Refugee Crisis [Updated]</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Ernesto Londo&#241;o			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2015-11-17T19:28:04+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">November 17, 2015 2:28 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">November 17, 2015 2:28 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//takingnote.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/11/17/the-vile-politics-of-the-syrian-refugee-crisis/" data-title="The Vile Politics of the Syrian Refugee Crisis [Updated]" data-description="As hundreds of thousands flee Syria, a growing number of American politicians are responding with unspeakable cruelty.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="w480"><figure class="media photo promo" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope="" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/11/17/opinion/17londonoWEB/17londonoWEB-blog480.jpg" itemtype="//schema.org/ImageObject" role="group"><span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span><div class="image"><img itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/11/17/opinion/17londonoWEB/17londonoWEB-blog480.jpg" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/11/17/opinion/17londonoWEB/17londonoWEB-blog480.jpg" id="100000004042635" width="480" height="338" alt="Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey."   /><meta itemprop="height" content="338"><meta itemprop="width" content="480"></div><figcaption class="caption" itemprop="description"><span class="caption-text">Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey.</span><span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span> John Raoux/Associated Press</span></figcaption></figure></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Since 1975, the United States <a href="//www.state.gov/j/prm/ra/">has resettled more than three million refugees</a>. They have contributed to the economy and culture of all 50 states.Â As hundreds of thousands of Syrians have fled their war-ravaged homeland, a growing number of American politicians â including <a href="//www.buzzfeed.com/kyleblaine/texas-governor-says-his-state-will-not-accept-syrian-refugee#.hvOppYzB4Z">more than half of the nationâs governors</a>Â â are responding with unspeakable cruelty.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Hereâs a sample of reactions:</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Asked whether he would allow orphaned refugees, <strong>Gov. Chris Christie of New Jersey</strong> said: âI donât think orphans under five are being, you know, should be admitted into the United States at this point.â</p>
<div class="w480">
<div class="w480 youtube-video-container">
<div class="youtube-video" data-youtube-id="TqAmDX5fGTU" data-start="">
<div class="thumb"><img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/TqAmDX5fGTU/0.jpg" />
<div class="playButton">
<div class="arrow"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Donald Trump</strong>, a leading Republican presidential candidate and the nationâs immigrant basher in chief, predictably joined the keep-em-out camp.</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet tw-hide-thread"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Refugees from Syria are now pouring into our great country. Who knows who they are &#8211; some could be ISIS. Is our president insane?</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â <a href="https://www.twitter.com/realDonaldTrump">Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump)</a> <a href="https://www.twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/666615398574530560" data-datetime="2015-11-17T13:54:30+00:00">17 Nov 15</a><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" id="platform_twitter_js" charset="utf-8"></script></p></blockquote>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Gov. Greg Abbott of Texas</strong> wrote a letter to President Obama saying Texas would not be welcoming to any new Syrian refugees. He warned that âopening our door to them irresponsibly exposes our fellow Americans to unspeakable peril.â</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet tw-hide-thread"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">My letter to @POTUS: Texas WILL NOT accept any Syrian refugees in the wake of the Paris attacks. https://t.co/GOALpfBD3X</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â <a href="https://www.twitter.com/GovAbbott">Gov. Greg Abbott (@GovAbbott)</a> <a href="https://www.twitter.com/GovAbbott/status/666275565138112512" data-datetime="2015-11-16T15:24:08+00:00">16 Nov 15</a></p></blockquote>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Gov. Rick Snyder of Michigan</strong>, which is home to one of the nationâs largest communities of Muslims, wrote a letter to Secretary of State John Kerry and Jeh Johnson, the Secretary of Homeland Security,Â urging a âfull reviewâ of the screening process for refugees.</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet tw-hide-thread"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Here is the letter that I sent to Secretary John Kerry and Secretary Jeh Johnson: https://t.co/IcW1OJxrlj https://t.co/kxJYnrXpwh</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â <a href="https://www.twitter.com/onetoughnerd">Governor Rick Snyder (@onetoughnerd)</a> <a href="https://www.twitter.com/onetoughnerd/status/666394083074531329" data-datetime="2015-11-16T23:15:05+00:00">16 Nov 15</a></p></blockquote>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Even though governors have no control over refugee admission policy, <strong>Gov. Bobby Jindal of Louisiana</strong> signed an executive order seeking to keep Syrian refugees out of his state.</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet tw-hide-thread"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">My letter to @POTUS: In light of Paris terrorist attacks, time to pause process of refugees coming to the US https://t.co/v2K7wuigX0</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â <a href="https://www.twitter.com/BobbyJindal">Gov. Bobby Jindal (@BobbyJindal)</a> <a href="https://www.twitter.com/BobbyJindal/status/665631665180381184" data-datetime="2015-11-14T20:45:30+00:00">14 Nov 15</a></p></blockquote>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">It is heartening that some governors, including <strong>Jay Inslee of Washington</strong>, took the opposite tack, saying their states would continue to welcome people fleeing war.</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet tw-hide-thread"><p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">WA continues to welcome those seeking refuge from persecution, no matter where they come from or their religion https://t.co/kT7dlJ4WJZ 3/3</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â <a href="https://www.twitter.com/GovInslee">Governor Jay Inslee (@GovInslee)</a> <a href="https://www.twitter.com/GovInslee/status/666347031678468096" data-datetime="2015-11-16T20:08:07+00:00">16 Nov 15</a></p></blockquote>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Update:Â Gov. Andrew Cuomo of New York</strong> <a href="//www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/cuojmo-keeping-refugees-defeat-american-dream-article-1.2437974">addressed the refugee crisis</a> during an appearance at Harvard on Tuesday.Â âWe have to protect Americans and we cannot lose our soul as America in the process,â he said. âThe day America says, âClose the gates, build the wall,â then I say take down the Statue of Liberty, because youâve gone to a different place.â</p>
